He periodically hears agreeable sounds via the ear… smells agreeable aromas via the nose… tastes agreeable flavors via the tongue… touches agreeable tactile sensations via the body.
An alms-collecting monk, while going for alms, is honored, respected, revered, venerated, and given homage.
“So, friends, let's become alms-collecting monks.
Then we, too, while going for alms, will periodically get to see agreeable sights via the eye… to hear agreeable sounds via the ear… to smell agreeable aromas via the nose… to taste agreeable flavors via the tongue… to touch agreeable tactile sensations via the body.
We, too, while going for alms, will be honored, respected, revered, venerated, and given homage.” And this discussion came to no conclusion.
